{"id":"idumaea","term":"Idumaea","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The Greek form of Edom (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 34:5\">Isa. 34:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 34:6\">6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 35:15\">Ezek. 35:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 36:5\">36:5</a>, but in R.V. “Edom”). (See EDOM).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Isaiah 34:5","Isaiah 34:6","Ezekiel 35:15","Ezekiel 36:5"]}